WEBVTT

00:05.092 --> 00:06.397
How do you
know Maggie?

00:06.441 --> 00:07.398
Uh, actually, I-I don't.
I'm just here with...

00:09.226 --> 00:10.401
Hi.

00:10.445 --> 00:12.012
...him.

00:12.055 --> 00:14.057
I think I just met
your ex-wife.

00:14.101 --> 00:16.364
Previously on
"A Million Little Things"...

00:16.407 --> 00:17.930
How can you be with him?

00:17.974 --> 00:20.063
After knowing
what he's capable of?

00:20.107 --> 00:22.109
I don't
trust Gary anymore,

00:22.152 --> 00:23.762
and, honestly,
I'm not sure I ever will.

00:23.806 --> 00:26.069
What do you think about
you coming with me?

00:26.113 --> 00:27.679
I'd love to meet
your friends.

00:27.723 --> 00:30.595
I just think right now
might not be the best time.

00:30.639 --> 00:32.032
Neil did things to me.

00:32.075 --> 00:33.033
Your brother?

00:33.076 --> 00:34.686
He hurt me, too.

00:34.730 --> 00:36.862
What?Ron, I know this is a lot.

00:36.906 --> 00:38.908
You knew what this man
was capable of

00:38.951 --> 00:40.866
and you let him
around our daughter?Dad, please --

00:44.348 --> 00:45.958
You alright?

00:46.002 --> 00:48.135
I think I felt a lump.

00:48.178 --> 00:49.745
♪♪

00:51.138 --> 00:53.227
Man: [ Over P.A. ] Dr. Kravitz,
please report to post-op.

00:53.270 --> 00:54.315
Dr. Kravitz.

00:54.358 --> 00:55.403
Maggie:
Unbelievable.

00:55.446 --> 00:57.361
The doctor said
three to four hours.

00:57.405 --> 00:59.450
It's been four hours
and five minutes.

00:59.494 --> 01:00.582
I'm sure they're just
looking Gary over

01:00.625 --> 01:02.279
to make sure they didn't

01:02.323 --> 01:03.889
leave an extra pair of scissors
in there or something.

01:05.326 --> 01:08.155
Mm-hmm. You see, what
we're trying to do is
make Maggie feel better.

01:08.198 --> 01:09.721
[ Exhales softly ][ Chuckles ]

01:09.765 --> 01:11.419
Do you know what
I just realized?

01:11.462 --> 01:13.029
We have now
been to the hospital

01:13.073 --> 01:14.291
for everyone
in this friend group.

01:14.335 --> 01:16.206
Huh. That's true.

01:16.250 --> 01:19.079
There's a green Jell-O for
whoever can put it in order.

01:19.122 --> 01:20.732
[ All chuckle ]Okay.

01:20.776 --> 01:22.256
I got it, I got it,
I got it.

01:22.299 --> 01:23.779
Maggie,
you led the way.

01:23.822 --> 01:24.997
Oh, thank you.

01:25.041 --> 01:27.087
It's an honor
just to be nominated.

01:27.130 --> 01:29.350
And then, babe, you had
the kidney stones.

01:29.393 --> 01:31.308
Oh! That's right. I forgot about
Rome's kidney stones.

01:31.352 --> 01:33.354
Yeah, I wish I could.
Haven't had a diet soda since.

01:33.397 --> 01:34.311
[ All chuckle ]

01:34.355 --> 01:35.921
And then Delilah
had the baby.

01:35.965 --> 01:37.619
Hold on, I get
half credit for that.

01:37.662 --> 01:39.664
Do you?Should you?

01:39.708 --> 01:41.188
Thank you.[ Laughs ]

01:41.231 --> 01:43.494
And then I got
the chair.

01:43.538 --> 01:45.540
Uh, Gina, you had
the concussion.
Oh.

01:45.583 --> 01:48.804
And then I had the
non-concussion with stitches.

01:48.847 --> 01:49.979
Maggie:
Whew. [ Sighs ]

01:50.022 --> 01:51.023
The next person we add
to this friend group

01:51.067 --> 01:52.547
should, uh,
probably be a doctor.

01:52.590 --> 01:53.591
[ Laughter ][ Door opens ]

01:53.635 --> 01:56.072
Speaking of which,
heads up.

01:56.116 --> 01:57.247
Woman: [ Over P.A. ]
Dr. Gray...

01:57.291 --> 01:58.814
[ Indistinct conversation ]

01:58.857 --> 02:02.034
Hey, folks, sorry that took
a little longer than I said.

02:02.078 --> 02:03.471
Oh, did it?

02:03.514 --> 02:05.603
The mass was embedded
a little deeper than we thought,

02:05.647 --> 02:07.953
but I feel confident
that we got it all.

02:07.997 --> 02:09.955
Does that mean
the cancer's gone?

02:09.999 --> 02:11.479
We won't know
until the results

02:11.522 --> 02:13.742
of the pathology report
come back.

02:13.785 --> 02:15.918
We should have that
in a day or two.

02:15.961 --> 02:17.137
He's in post-op
for a few more minutes,

02:17.180 --> 02:18.660
and then you can
go in and see him.

02:18.703 --> 02:20.270
Okay. Thanks.

02:21.184 --> 02:22.664
Rome: Hey, Doc...

02:22.707 --> 02:23.882
what are you doing Friday?

02:23.926 --> 02:25.493
You wanna come to
a game night?

02:25.536 --> 02:26.798
[ P.A. beeps]

02:26.842 --> 02:28.191
Dr. Jacobs
to the nurses' station.

02:28.235 --> 02:29.540
I'm being paged.

02:29.584 --> 02:31.194
[ Laughter ]

02:31.238 --> 02:33.501
I thought we were adding
a doctor to our friend group.

02:33.544 --> 02:35.416
So she's good enough
to save our friend,

02:35.459 --> 02:37.200
but not good enough
to play Scattergories?

02:37.244 --> 02:40.334
[ Laughter ]I-I don't think she wants
to play Scattergories.

02:40.377 --> 02:42.074
♪♪

02:47.123 --> 02:48.255
Man: [ Over television ]
More rain tomorrow.

02:48.298 --> 02:49.865
Woman: Coming up next on...

02:49.908 --> 02:52.520
No, no, no.
Come on, Harrison.

02:52.563 --> 02:54.130
[ Indistinct chatter
on television]I'm begging you.

02:54.174 --> 02:55.479
I'm almost out of here.

02:55.523 --> 02:57.438
You'll have that remote
all to yourself.

02:57.481 --> 02:59.744
I cannot watch another
home makeover show.

02:59.788 --> 03:01.746
I need to see
how this one plays out.

03:01.790 --> 03:03.400
In that last one,
they put carpeting

03:03.444 --> 03:05.315
over those
beautiful hardwood floors.

03:05.359 --> 03:08.318
[ Sighs ]
It was like
a hate crime on my screen.

03:08.362 --> 03:09.928
Besides,
you already used your veto

03:09.972 --> 03:11.060
for the Game Show Network.

03:11.103 --> 03:12.975
Yeah, because
that show's from the '70s.

03:13.018 --> 03:15.325
It's tough to get invested
when the jackpot

03:15.369 --> 03:17.109
they're competing for
is $75

03:17.153 --> 03:19.242
and a cold sore
from Richard Dawson.

03:19.286 --> 03:21.026
Good morning.

03:21.070 --> 03:23.725
Okay, I know I said
I would wear the nurse outfit,

03:23.768 --> 03:26.162
but when I put it on,
the fishnets made my legs all --

03:26.206 --> 03:27.642
[ Laughs awkwardly ]

03:27.685 --> 03:30.297
And you apparently don't
have your own room anymore.

03:30.340 --> 03:32.081
Hi.Harrison, this is, uh --

03:32.124 --> 03:33.735
Oh, no.
I know exactly who you are.

03:33.778 --> 03:35.563
I listen to you
all the time.

03:35.606 --> 03:38.870
I cannot believe I'm literally
in the room with Dr. Bloom.

03:38.914 --> 03:41.046
Um, wait a minute.

03:41.090 --> 03:42.570
That means that you play
for the Bruins.

03:43.571 --> 03:44.659
Um...No, no, no, Bloom.

03:44.702 --> 03:45.747
Let me have this, please.Mm.

03:45.790 --> 03:48.271
Yeah, yeah.
Y-You caught me.

03:48.315 --> 03:50.186
I -- You know, I'm trying
to keep a low profile.

03:50.230 --> 03:51.970
Yeah, I-I'm sorry
I didn't recognize you.

03:52.014 --> 03:53.145
It's cool.

03:53.189 --> 03:55.147
These are the moments
that keep me humble.

03:55.191 --> 03:56.105
[ Wheelchair clacking ]

03:56.148 --> 03:57.628
Sorry for the wait.

03:57.672 --> 03:59.761
Just needed a wheelchair
to free up.

03:59.804 --> 04:02.024
Don't want to hear
that backstory.

04:02.067 --> 04:03.547
Uh, we can't leave yet.

04:03.591 --> 04:05.636
Uh, the doctor hasn't given us
the pathology report.

04:05.680 --> 04:07.290
Sorry, yeah.

04:07.334 --> 04:08.813
Unfortunately, the lab
is pretty backed up right now,

04:08.857 --> 04:10.293
but they said they'll get to it
first thing tomorrow.

04:10.337 --> 04:11.686
[ Sighing ] Okay.

04:11.729 --> 04:12.687
The doctor made you
an appointment

04:12.730 --> 04:13.992
at 9:00 a.m. at his office.

04:14.036 --> 04:16.908
Great. [ Sighs ]
Another fun day of waiting.

04:16.952 --> 04:19.607
Cancer's the best,
am I right?

04:19.650 --> 04:22.784
I'd love to stick around,
but she's my ride.

04:22.827 --> 04:24.307
Thanks for supporting the team,
Harrison.

04:24.351 --> 04:25.613
[ Chuckles ]Nice to meet you.

04:25.656 --> 04:27.615
Yeah, it was.
Go B's!

04:27.658 --> 04:29.269
Woman: [ Over P.A. ]
Dr. Phelps to oncology.

04:29.312 --> 04:32.054
Eddie: I can't believe it,
but it's been a year.

04:32.097 --> 04:35.884
And, uh, while I am grateful
for this,

04:35.927 --> 04:40.236
I'm also aware that, at one
point, I had my 13-year chip.

04:40.280 --> 04:42.586
And I know I'm supposed
to take it a day at a time,

04:42.630 --> 04:46.242
but, uh, a couple of weeks ago,

04:46.286 --> 04:48.592
I found out that my buddy's
cancer might be back,

04:48.636 --> 04:53.728
and, um, I can't say that
my first instinct

04:53.771 --> 04:55.556
wasn't to try
to numb the pain.

04:55.599 --> 04:58.341
♪♪

04:58.385 --> 05:01.649
But I didn't.

05:01.692 --> 05:05.261
Instead, I-I've been focusing on
the positive parts of my life.

05:05.305 --> 05:06.915
[ Sighs ]

05:06.958 --> 05:11.702
Like the woman
I've been seeing, my...

05:11.746 --> 05:13.051
Anna.

05:13.095 --> 05:15.576
You know, Eddie, the program
strongly suggests

05:15.619 --> 05:16.925
that you wait until --

05:16.968 --> 05:18.927
I know, I'm not supposed
to date anyone

05:18.970 --> 05:19.884
until I've been sober
for a year.

05:19.928 --> 05:20.972
But it is new.

05:21.016 --> 05:22.191
We've been taking it
very slowly.

05:22.234 --> 05:24.324
[ Chuckles ]
For a lot of reasons.

05:24.367 --> 05:27.892
And...

05:27.936 --> 05:30.852
I've just really been
in a good place,

05:30.895 --> 05:33.376
and she's helped me
get there.

05:33.420 --> 05:34.899
Well, if it
doesn't work out,

05:34.943 --> 05:37.162
I'd still like to
set you up with my niece.

05:37.206 --> 05:38.816
If I date your niece,
I can't date you.

05:38.860 --> 05:39.904
[ Laughs ]

05:39.948 --> 05:42.516
[ Laughter ]Oh, you.

05:42.559 --> 05:44.387
Look at her,
just giggling.

05:44.431 --> 05:45.867
There's no support group
for that.

05:45.910 --> 05:47.259
[ Laughter ]

05:47.303 --> 05:50.219
♪♪

05:50.262 --> 05:52.395
Wait, wait.
When we play Celebrity later,

05:52.439 --> 05:54.266
how many clues
should each person get?

05:54.310 --> 05:56.312
[ Peeling quickly ]I can't believe how juvenile
my parents are being!

05:57.444 --> 05:58.706
So...five?

05:58.749 --> 06:00.490
It's been
almost two weeks,

06:00.534 --> 06:02.927
and my mom is still
a total mess.

06:02.971 --> 06:05.365
How could he tell her that
what Neil did was her fault?

06:05.408 --> 06:09.151
Well, in your dad's defense --
treading lightly here --

06:09.194 --> 06:12.415
he just found out a piece
of shocking information

06:12.459 --> 06:15.070
about something that Neil did
to both you and your mom.

06:15.113 --> 06:17.028
It's a lot to take in.

06:17.072 --> 06:18.290
I know when
I first found out,

06:18.334 --> 06:20.162
it took me more than
a minute to process it.

06:20.205 --> 06:22.556
No, I get that,
but my mom is devastated,

06:22.599 --> 06:24.340
and my dad
blaming her for it

06:24.384 --> 06:25.776
is only making things
harder on her,

06:25.820 --> 06:27.691
which is making things
harder on me.

06:27.735 --> 06:29.301
But I thought you said
that your dad was great

06:29.345 --> 06:31.695
when he called you earlier
to find out how you were doing.

06:31.739 --> 06:34.045
Yeah, he was great
with mystuff.

06:34.089 --> 06:35.917
But the second I brought up Mom,
he just lost it.

06:35.960 --> 06:38.006
And now, they both want me
to take their side.

06:38.049 --> 06:39.181
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

06:39.224 --> 06:41.879
Oh. Is that my mom
calling to make sure

06:41.923 --> 06:43.315
that I don't
blame her for this,

06:43.359 --> 06:45.013
or my dad calling
to make sure I do?

06:45.056 --> 06:46.014
Ooh.

06:46.057 --> 06:47.885
Hello?

06:47.929 --> 06:49.452
No, I told you
I'm not mad at you.

06:49.496 --> 06:50.932
Hey, Shelly.

06:50.975 --> 06:53.369
Shelly: Is that Rome? Mm-hmm.

06:53.413 --> 06:55.066
Did you tell him
what your father said?

06:55.110 --> 06:57.068
Actually, Mom,
Rome just told me that

06:57.112 --> 06:59.549
when he first found out what
Neil did, he was angry, too.

06:59.593 --> 07:01.551
At me? Would it help
if I talked to him?

07:01.595 --> 07:04.554
No, not at you.
At the fact that it happened.

07:04.598 --> 07:06.774
I'm sure that's
what Dad's feeling, too.

07:06.817 --> 07:09.385
[ Sighs ]
Well, I wouldn't know,

07:09.429 --> 07:11.126
because the man's
not comfortable

07:11.169 --> 07:12.780
expressing his feelings,

07:12.823 --> 07:15.086
or being around anyone else
expressing theirs.

07:15.130 --> 07:16.653
Have you tried
calling him?

07:16.697 --> 07:19.003
Honestly, the way
we left things,

07:19.047 --> 07:20.918
it seemed like
he didn't want to talk to me.

07:20.962 --> 07:22.006
[ Softly ] Since when has that
ever stopped you?

07:22.050 --> 07:22.833
What'd he say?

07:24.531 --> 07:27.316
He said, "Don't let that
stop you."

07:27.359 --> 07:28.883
He's right.

07:28.926 --> 07:31.189
I'm gonna call your father
as soon as we hang up.

07:31.233 --> 07:32.887
Great.

07:32.930 --> 07:35.803
What should I say?

07:35.846 --> 07:37.369
Mom, I can't do this
right now.

07:37.413 --> 07:39.502
We have a bunch of people
coming over for game night.

07:39.546 --> 07:40.721
Is your dad coming?

07:40.764 --> 07:42.287
No. Because I love games.

07:42.331 --> 07:43.854
Mom, you're --
it's just for our friends.

07:43.898 --> 07:46.030
Well, honey, I'd like
to think that we're --

07:46.074 --> 07:47.510
Mom, you're not
coming over for dinner.

07:47.554 --> 07:49.120
It's dinner too?Mom!

07:49.164 --> 07:50.731
I gotta go.
Love you. Bye.No, w-wait --

07:50.774 --> 07:52.820
[ Line beeps][ Sighs ] Okay.

07:52.863 --> 07:54.952
Love you.

07:54.996 --> 07:56.606
[ Line ringing, beep]Katherine:
Hey, Eddie.

07:56.650 --> 07:59.130
Hey. I just wanted to
give you the heads up

07:59.174 --> 08:00.436
before the party tonight,

08:00.480 --> 08:02.525
since I didn't give you
the heads up last time.

08:02.569 --> 08:04.092
I'm bringing Anna
to game night...

08:04.135 --> 08:05.746
Oh, well,
thanks for letting me --

08:05.789 --> 08:08.531
...where, full disclosure,
we are gonna crush everyone.

08:08.575 --> 08:10.185
[ Chuckles ]

08:10.228 --> 08:11.969
Well, the teams haven't
been decided yet,

08:12.013 --> 08:14.363
but I appreciate
the heads up.

08:14.406 --> 08:16.539
And just to give you
the heads up,

08:16.583 --> 08:18.019
I'm bringing Greta.

08:18.062 --> 08:20.108
Oh,
my sister's coming?

08:20.151 --> 08:21.762
Okay.
You have to stop doing that.

08:21.805 --> 08:23.372
But it's too fun.[ Scoffs ]

08:23.415 --> 08:25.766
Seriously, though,
I'm glad she's gonna be there.

08:25.809 --> 08:27.985
I didn't realize
you'd told everyone.

08:28.029 --> 08:30.074
I haven't.

08:30.118 --> 08:32.642
They're -- They're just gonna
find out when we get there.

08:32.686 --> 08:35.210
Well, in that case, I will
not be fashionably late.

08:35.253 --> 08:36.124
[ Chuckles ]

08:36.167 --> 08:36.907
[ Whispering ]
Who's that?

08:36.951 --> 08:37.995
It's Eddie.

08:38.039 --> 08:39.388
[ Gasps ]
Oh! What's up, big bro?

08:39.431 --> 08:41.259
Okay. That's it.

08:41.303 --> 08:44.393
You two are not allowed to be
on each other's teams.

08:44.436 --> 08:45.263
Eddie and Greta: You're the one
who switched teams.

08:45.307 --> 08:46.743
Oh-ho-ho!

08:46.787 --> 08:47.918
Jinx!
You owe me a Coke.

08:47.962 --> 08:49.572
Ohh!
Ohhhhhhh!

08:49.616 --> 08:51.182
Okay.
Goodbye.

08:51.226 --> 08:52.444
Bye.

08:52.488 --> 08:54.446
Oh, my gosh.[ Both chuckle ]

08:54.490 --> 08:55.622
Oh, thanks.

08:55.665 --> 08:57.580
Hey, uh...

08:57.624 --> 08:58.755
Tonight when
I meet your friends,

08:58.799 --> 09:00.670
do you want me
to tone down all this?

09:00.714 --> 09:02.237
Absolutely not.

09:02.280 --> 09:03.978
I want them to experience you
exactly the way I have.

09:04.021 --> 09:04.979
Oh, really?

09:05.022 --> 09:06.328
I mean --
[ Chuckles ]

09:06.371 --> 09:08.069
Like, exactly?
No,
let me rephrase that.

09:08.112 --> 09:09.331
You know
what I mean.

09:09.374 --> 09:10.593
Please stop.
Different
kind of party.

09:10.637 --> 09:12.247
♪♪

09:12.290 --> 09:15.555
Okay.
What do you think?

09:15.598 --> 09:17.600
One better, or two?

09:17.644 --> 09:20.429
Uh...they're both great.

09:20.472 --> 09:22.997
Oh, okay, well, perfect.
I'll just wear them both.

09:23.040 --> 09:24.651
Come on, Eddie,
I want to look good.

09:24.694 --> 09:26.043
You always look good.

09:26.087 --> 09:27.871
Besides, my friends
have already met you.

09:27.915 --> 09:29.351
They know
how good you look.

09:29.394 --> 09:31.614
Well, I'm not sure that
they remember that part.

09:31.658 --> 09:34.965
What they probably remember is
how I yelled at Maggie

09:35.009 --> 09:36.880
in the parking lot
of a convenience store

09:36.924 --> 09:38.534
and then I stormed out
of her birthday party.

09:38.578 --> 09:40.231
Which is why, tonight,
I really --

09:40.275 --> 09:44.540
I just want to make a good
third first impression.

09:44.584 --> 09:45.976
Well, in that case,
not the cardigan.

09:46.020 --> 09:47.456
Okay, thank you.

09:47.499 --> 09:49.414
[ Sighs ] It's too bad
Sophie's on tour.

09:49.458 --> 09:51.634
It'd be nice to have someone
at the party that likes me.

09:51.678 --> 09:54.115
You do know
I'm gonna be there, right?

09:54.158 --> 09:57.422
And in case it wasn't clear,
I like you.

09:57.466 --> 09:58.946
Mm.

09:58.989 --> 10:01.252
Besides, even if
she wasn't on tour,

10:01.296 --> 10:04.038
there's no way she would show up
to a game night with Gary.

10:04.081 --> 10:06.475
That's true.

10:06.518 --> 10:08.042
You sure you don't
like the cardigan?

10:08.085 --> 10:10.348
If I say I love it,
can we move on to the pants?

10:10.392 --> 10:14.004
Oh, not even close.
We still have jewelry to do.

10:14.048 --> 10:16.485
You do know game night's
tonight, right?

10:17.529 --> 10:18.966
[ Door shuts ]

10:19.009 --> 10:20.663
You're back.

10:20.707 --> 10:21.882
Yeah.
What did the doctor say?

10:21.925 --> 10:23.927
We won't get the results
until tomorrow.

10:23.971 --> 10:25.320
Hey. Hey.
[ Smooches ]

10:25.363 --> 10:29.106
Wait, wait, wait, wait.
Something's different.

10:29.150 --> 10:33.110
How come
it smells...clean?

10:33.154 --> 10:34.938
And why are you
taking out the trash?

10:34.982 --> 10:36.636
What did you break?

10:36.679 --> 10:37.985
Nothing.

10:38.028 --> 10:40.291
I-I just didn't want you
to have to do it.

10:40.335 --> 10:43.686
I also folded all your laundry
that wasn't underwear.

10:43.730 --> 10:45.688
Also, shouldn't you have
more underwear?

10:45.732 --> 10:47.603
Ha! Alright, listen up,
Mother Hen.

