22:18.511 --> 22:20.687
Go team.
Yo.
Okay, Anna, you're up.

22:20.730 --> 22:23.211
We're down by 12.
No pressure.

22:23.254 --> 22:24.125
[ Cheers and applause ]Gary: Let's go, squad.

22:24.168 --> 22:25.561
Anna: Zero pressure.

22:25.605 --> 22:26.910
And go![ Timer beeps ]

22:26.954 --> 22:28.172
Okay, okay,
it's -- it's that, um --

22:28.216 --> 22:28.999
oh, you know, that thing.

22:29.043 --> 22:30.044
[ Choking sounds ]

22:30.087 --> 22:30.871
Need
more information.

22:30.914 --> 22:32.742
You know that thing...

22:32.786 --> 22:34.265
Say more words.
Just more words.

22:34.309 --> 22:35.397
Ideally that form
a sentence.

22:35.441 --> 22:36.833
[ Stammers ]
Okay, pass.

22:36.877 --> 22:38.269
Oh, no! Every time you pass,
we lose a point.

22:38.313 --> 22:40.489
What? Pass.Stop passing!

22:40.533 --> 22:42.056
Okay, okay, so this is --

22:42.099 --> 22:44.667
it -- it's not the sad
Green Giant, it's...

22:44.711 --> 22:46.147
Oh, you can't say
"Green" or "Giant."

22:46.190 --> 22:47.627
Oh!

22:47.670 --> 22:50.369
Okay, okay, so, this is
the first person to want --

22:50.412 --> 22:52.675
And time!
Wow!

22:52.719 --> 22:54.285
Great job.
Great job.

22:54.329 --> 22:56.418
Sorry.
I'm so sorry.

22:56.462 --> 22:58.464
I'm so sorry.Barely matters.

22:58.507 --> 23:01.336
The stupid timer...Good effort.
It was a good effort.

23:01.380 --> 23:02.511
You guys are sweet.

23:02.555 --> 23:04.426
Okay. Ed, you're up.
Come on, lover boy.

23:04.470 --> 23:05.775
[ Laughing ] Yeah,
here we go, here we go.

23:05.819 --> 23:07.995
Sorry.
Gary: That's all right.

23:08.038 --> 23:10.040
We're about to get it back
with this.Greta: Yeah.

23:10.084 --> 23:11.694
Eddie: Oh, thank you.

23:11.738 --> 23:13.783
Katherine, yeah?

23:13.827 --> 23:14.871
You ready, huh?

23:14.915 --> 23:16.960
Born ready, Eduardo!
Let's do this!

23:17.004 --> 23:17.874
[ Rome laughs ]

23:17.918 --> 23:20.703
I am also ready.[ Laughter ]

23:20.747 --> 23:22.966
Regina: Dad, I need you
to apologize to Mom.

23:23.010 --> 23:25.447
I will absolutely
not apologize to her.

23:25.491 --> 23:28.755
She should apologize
to me and to you.

23:28.798 --> 23:29.973
I mean, this was not
some stranger --

23:30.017 --> 23:31.061
this was her brother.

23:31.105 --> 23:32.759
She knew
and she didn't protect you.

23:32.802 --> 23:35.109
Dad, that's just it.
She didn't know.

23:35.152 --> 23:36.763
She said
he did it to her, too.

23:36.806 --> 23:38.547
She blocked it out.

23:38.591 --> 23:39.896
I know what she's trying
to make you believe,

23:39.940 --> 23:42.638
but you don't just forget
something like that.

23:42.682 --> 23:45.032
Dad, do you know how old Mom was
when Neil first did that to her?

23:46.599 --> 23:48.557
She was 7.

23:48.601 --> 23:50.472
She couldn't
protect herself,

23:50.516 --> 23:53.606
so her subconscious did the only
thing it could to protect her --

23:53.649 --> 23:56.696
it erased it
from her memory.

23:56.739 --> 23:58.175
And I know she's
telling the truth,

23:58.219 --> 24:00.047
because I did the same thing
after he did it to me.

24:00.090 --> 24:01.657
[ Hands thud ]
Neil took something from me

24:01.701 --> 24:05.574
I didn't even know
that I had.

24:05.618 --> 24:06.923
Okay?

24:06.967 --> 24:08.925
He was the first man
that ever touched me.

24:08.969 --> 24:16.585
♪♪

24:16.629 --> 24:20.502
Gina,
I'm so sorry.

24:20.546 --> 24:22.635
Ishould have
been there for you.

24:22.678 --> 24:27.640
♪♪

24:27.683 --> 24:28.902
Dad.
[ Clears throat ]

24:28.945 --> 24:32.166
Look at me.

24:32.209 --> 24:35.082
I'm not that little girl
anymore.

24:38.694 --> 24:41.088
And, honestly,
for a while,

24:41.131 --> 24:43.438
it wasreally hard...

24:43.482 --> 24:45.875
to deal with it,

24:45.919 --> 24:50.227
to come to terms
with it.

24:50.271 --> 24:54.188
But who I am now is stronger
than I have ever been.

24:54.231 --> 24:55.668
[ Sniffles ]

24:55.711 --> 24:58.540
And I feel like every minute
I spend wondering

24:58.584 --> 25:04.677
what could've gone differently
gives him the power back.

25:07.375 --> 25:08.594
He doesn't deserve that.

25:08.637 --> 25:10.204
[ Sniffles ]

25:10.247 --> 25:12.423
That's mine.

25:12.467 --> 25:17.820
♪♪

25:17.864 --> 25:19.518
Stop punishing yourself
for something

25:19.561 --> 25:22.042
you don't deserve
to be punished for.

25:22.085 --> 25:23.696
It's not your fault.

25:23.739 --> 25:26.176
♪♪

25:26.220 --> 25:28.439
And it's not Mom's,
either.

25:28.483 --> 25:37.448
♪♪

25:37.492 --> 25:41.104
Let me start by thanking whoever
folded their strips in fourths.

25:41.148 --> 25:43.019
What, are we playing games
or doing origami here?

25:43.063 --> 25:46.632
[ Loud laughter ]

25:46.675 --> 25:47.676
Yeah, alright,
Mendez.

25:47.720 --> 25:49.939
Only need 17 to tie.

25:49.983 --> 25:51.985
Alright. [ Sighs ]
We ready over there?

25:52.028 --> 25:52.725
Okay.[ Timer beeps ]

25:52.768 --> 25:54.378
And here we go.

25:54.422 --> 25:55.205
Uh, Bamm-Bamm.

25:55.249 --> 25:56.729
Lone Ranger!

25:56.772 --> 25:57.730
What?

25:57.773 --> 25:59.035
Uh, the guns --
b-bam, bam.

25:59.079 --> 26:00.167
No, uh,
modern Stone Age family.

26:00.210 --> 26:01.342
Fred Flintstone!Yes!

26:01.385 --> 26:03.039
No, agh, I said "stone."
It doesn't count.

26:03.083 --> 26:04.519
No, no, you're --
Actually, that's okay.

26:04.563 --> 26:06.652
We got it when you said
"Bamm-Bamm." That's a point.

26:06.695 --> 26:08.392
And you know what?
I'm still talking,

26:08.436 --> 26:09.829
so I'm adding 10 seconds
to your time.

26:09.872 --> 26:10.743
No, wh-what are you doing?[ Timer beeps ]

26:10.786 --> 26:11.700
Alright, fine, 15.

26:11.744 --> 26:14.007
[ Timer beeps ]Guys, stop.

26:14.050 --> 26:15.312
Do you want to play
something else?

26:15.356 --> 26:16.966
We can totally
play something else.
Please.

26:17.010 --> 26:18.620
What should we play?
Um, maybe --Quiplash?

26:18.664 --> 26:19.665
Yes, that is exactly
what I was thinking!

26:19.708 --> 26:20.666
Yeah,
you love Quiplash.

26:20.709 --> 26:21.928
Of course it was.

26:21.971 --> 26:23.233
Just cut it out,
all of you, okay?!

26:23.277 --> 26:24.365
I see what you're doing,
and it's super sweet,

26:24.408 --> 26:26.280
but it's very annoying.

26:26.323 --> 26:27.324
I don't want to think
about tomorrow.

26:27.368 --> 26:28.630
I came here
to play games with

26:28.674 --> 26:31.154
my self-indulgent,
often thoughtless friends.

26:31.198 --> 26:33.766
So will you please, please,
go back to being those people

26:33.809 --> 26:36.812
so that we can just have
a normal night, please?

26:40.555 --> 26:43.819
Well, since you said it
[coughs] you did say "stone."

26:43.863 --> 26:45.647
And ain't nobody get it
off of Bamm-Bamm.

26:45.691 --> 26:47.649
Thank you.

26:47.693 --> 26:48.868
[ Timer beeping ]

26:48.911 --> 26:51.087
Oh, that's
my asparagus tarts.

26:51.131 --> 26:52.611
No, wait.
I think it's the brownies.

26:52.654 --> 26:54.090
You know, I should've got
Gina to write it down.

26:54.134 --> 26:56.658
No, my nose is telling me
the cheese is burning.

26:56.702 --> 26:57.920
Oh, that's my brie,
dude.

26:57.964 --> 27:00.009
Wait up.[ Doorbell rings ]

27:00.053 --> 27:01.968
Hey, you definitely seem like
you've got that under control,

27:02.011 --> 27:04.666
so I'll get the door.[ Oven door opens ]

27:04.710 --> 27:07.103
You guys keep playing.[ Oven door closes ]

27:07.147 --> 27:10.280
Save your Lactaid, everyone,
because this is a mess.

27:10.324 --> 27:12.413
[ Indistinct conversations ]

27:12.456 --> 27:15.155
♪♪

27:15.198 --> 27:17.244
Hi.

27:17.287 --> 27:18.593
Hi.

27:23.424 --> 27:25.818
Uh, Rome's inside.

27:25.861 --> 27:27.210
Let me, uh --
I'll grab him.

27:27.254 --> 27:35.131
♪♪

27:35.175 --> 27:36.655
[ Sighs ]

27:36.698 --> 27:39.179
Danny came
to my concert tonight.

27:39.222 --> 27:40.789
[ Sighs ]

27:40.833 --> 27:43.270
When do you
get the results?

27:43.313 --> 27:46.447
Um...

27:46.490 --> 27:48.667
not till tomorrow.

27:48.710 --> 27:51.017
You didn't
have to come.

27:51.060 --> 27:53.062
You have every right to be
mad at me, and I --

27:53.106 --> 27:54.803
I don't want this
to be the reason you --

27:54.847 --> 27:56.152
No, it's not.

27:56.196 --> 28:01.027
It's just another reminder
that life is short.

28:01.070 --> 28:04.247
And I don't have time
to not have you in mine.

28:04.291 --> 28:07.381
♪♪

28:07.424 --> 28:09.209
I still don't like
what you did,

28:09.252 --> 28:13.213
and I never will,

28:13.256 --> 28:19.523
but I care about you
more than I am mad at you.

28:19.567 --> 28:21.351
And if you
don't have cancer,

28:21.395 --> 28:24.050
I still reserve the right
to be pissed at you again.

28:24.093 --> 28:25.616
[ Both laugh ]

28:25.660 --> 28:27.575
That's fair.
[ Sighs ]

28:30.578 --> 28:36.018
But if I do have cancer
and it's terminal,

28:36.062 --> 28:37.933
you just say the word,
and I will kill Peter.

28:37.977 --> 28:42.242
[ Both chuckle ]

28:42.285 --> 28:43.460
You missed me.I missed you.

28:43.504 --> 28:44.505
Yeah, I missed you.

28:44.548 --> 28:45.985
Anna: Here we go.[ Chuckles ]

28:46.028 --> 28:48.204
Okay, okay, okay. So this is --
this is one of my clues.

28:48.248 --> 28:50.206
Oh, you can't say that.Eddie: Oh, it's okay,
just keep going. It's fine.

28:50.250 --> 28:52.252
Wait, wait. Come here.Ooh! I love this one.

28:52.295 --> 28:54.558
Rome: Great!
Start giving clues.Y-You gotta see this.

28:54.602 --> 28:55.777
Okay, it's the -- it's the movie
with the DeLorean.

28:55.821 --> 28:57.039
"Back to the Future"!Yeah.

28:57.083 --> 28:58.171
And you can say,
"Back to the Future."

28:58.214 --> 28:59.302
Okay, so it's
the kid from that movie.

28:59.346 --> 29:00.477
Michael J. Fox.

29:00.521 --> 29:01.870
And you can say
"Back to the Future."

29:01.914 --> 29:03.393
But not the actor's name,
the character's name.

29:03.437 --> 29:04.786
Marty McFly!

29:04.830 --> 29:06.745
Yes![ All cheering ]

29:06.788 --> 29:08.181
-Yes!
-You got one!

29:08.224 --> 29:10.661
Okay, okay, so -- so,
the first name is Marty.

29:10.705 --> 29:12.794
And...time!

29:12.838 --> 29:14.665
No.

29:14.709 --> 29:15.928
It was Martin Scorsese.

29:15.971 --> 29:17.538
Wow.
Yeah.

29:17.581 --> 29:19.061
That's --
I'm the worst.

29:19.105 --> 29:20.759
Rome: You could've just said
it was "Goodfellas," but...

29:20.802 --> 29:22.151
Sophie: Hi.

29:26.329 --> 29:28.941
She's with me.

29:28.984 --> 29:30.681
[ Chuckles ][ Bottle thuds ]

29:30.725 --> 29:31.944
And, Katherine,
you thought yourdate

29:31.987 --> 29:34.033
was gonna be the biggest
surprise of the night.

29:34.076 --> 29:35.469
Oh --
Oh, no!

29:35.512 --> 29:36.775
Okay.
Oh, no!Rome: Whoa.

29:36.818 --> 29:38.211
It's -- It's okay.Oh, my God!

29:38.254 --> 29:39.734
Oh, my God.
I'm so sorry.

29:39.778 --> 29:41.214
Hey, Eddie,
are you okay?

29:41.257 --> 29:42.824
We should probably get the
alcohol off the alcoholic.

29:42.868 --> 29:44.652
Oh, Rome, your carpet!Paper towels coming up.

29:44.695 --> 29:46.088
Yeah, yeah, Ed, you can wear
one of my shirts.

29:46.132 --> 29:48.047
It's not that bad,
guys.

29:48.090 --> 29:49.744
Um, actually, I think you
should. I'm gonna go get one.

29:49.788 --> 29:51.702
Oh, God.
I'm so sorry, babe.

29:51.746 --> 29:53.530
It's fine. Dry clean.I'm so sorry.

29:53.574 --> 29:55.750
Oh, no.

29:55.794 --> 29:57.665
[ Gasps ] Oh, the carpet.
Look at the carpet!Be -- Be careful, though.

29:57.708 --> 29:59.058
Be careful.

29:59.101 --> 30:00.363
That's, like, a --

30:00.407 --> 30:02.191
sort of an aggressive way
to pick up glass.

30:02.235 --> 30:03.323
Oh, God!
No, just --

30:04.890 --> 30:05.891
[ Bag clatters ]

30:08.110 --> 30:09.633
Hey.

30:09.677 --> 30:11.331
Hey.

30:13.333 --> 30:16.553
[ Sighs ]
I'm really sorry.

30:16.597 --> 30:19.643
Just when I heard you and Gary
were getting back together,

30:19.687 --> 30:22.298
I just --
I freaked out.

30:22.342 --> 30:25.824
No, Soph, I'm sorry.

30:25.867 --> 30:28.217
Believe me, I never wanted you
to find out that way.

30:28.261 --> 30:29.566
I know.

30:33.483 --> 30:38.010
Listen, I'm sure you guys are
gonna get good results tomorrow,

30:38.053 --> 30:40.664
but I just wanted to say
that no matter what happens,

30:40.708 --> 30:42.231
I'm here for you,

30:42.275 --> 30:44.407
just like
you were there for me.

30:44.451 --> 30:47.454
And I realize as I say that,
I've said that to you before,

30:47.497 --> 30:48.890
but this time I mean it.

30:48.934 --> 30:50.892
[ Both chuckle ]

30:50.936 --> 30:55.157
♪♪

30:55.201 --> 30:56.724
Hey, hey.
It's okay.

30:56.767 --> 31:00.162
♪♪

31:00.206 --> 31:01.685
But what if it's not?

31:01.729 --> 31:04.340
♪♪

31:04.384 --> 31:06.255
Rome: What's mine is yours,
unless it's designer.

31:06.299 --> 31:08.605
And don't touch
my facial cream.

31:08.649 --> 31:10.999
Hey, man, I'm -- I'm
sorry about treating you
differently earlier, bro.

31:11.043 --> 31:12.783
I was just trying --
I'm fine.

31:14.394 --> 31:16.439
You sure?
Yeah.

31:16.483 --> 31:19.312
Yeah. Yeah, yeah.

31:19.355 --> 31:21.792
I mean,
I thought I was,

31:21.836 --> 31:24.578
but I'm not so sure.

31:24.621 --> 31:25.753
With Sophie
showing up...

31:27.407 --> 31:30.323
Yeah, I-I-I didn't realize
you two had worked things out.

31:30.366 --> 31:32.368
We hadn't.

31:32.412 --> 31:33.979
Danny told her.

31:34.022 --> 31:35.328
Well, I wish it were
for a better reason,

31:35.371 --> 31:38.984
but Sophie being back
is good, right?

31:39.027 --> 31:41.160
Yeah. Yeah, yeah, yeah.
It's great.

31:41.203 --> 31:44.990
It's just, uh, I don't know
if you've noticed,

31:45.033 --> 31:48.950
but sometimes I can lean
towards glass half empty.

31:48.994 --> 31:49.951
No,
haven't noticed at all.

31:49.995 --> 31:52.780
[ Both chuckle ]

31:52.823 --> 31:56.827
And the reason
that I do that --

31:56.871 --> 31:58.829
and I know this is gonna
sound crazy --

31:58.873 --> 32:00.919
but there is
a part of me that thinks

32:00.962 --> 32:03.965
if I act like my cancer's
gonna come back,

32:04.009 --> 32:06.098
it'll keep my cancer
from coming back.

32:06.141 --> 32:09.797
♪♪

32:09.840 --> 32:11.668
So when Maggie found
the lump on me,

32:11.712 --> 32:12.931
I mean, sure,
I was nervous,

32:12.974 --> 32:15.194
but there was this voice
in the back of my head

32:15.237 --> 32:18.849
that kept telling me,
"There is no way it's back."

32:18.893 --> 32:21.852
♪♪

32:21.896 --> 32:23.942
And that voice told me
the same thing

32:23.985 --> 32:26.379
during my CAT scan
and my surgery.

32:26.422 --> 32:29.991
And even when the nurse said
we couldn't get the results yet,

32:30.035 --> 32:36.171
deep down, I was like,
"It's fine.

32:36.215 --> 32:37.956
You're fine."

32:37.999 --> 32:40.741
♪♪

32:40.784 --> 32:44.701
Now, with
Sophie coming back...

32:44.745 --> 32:49.010
♪♪

32:49.054 --> 32:53.275
♪♪

32:53.319 --> 32:55.234
...I'm really scared.

32:55.277 --> 32:58.889
♪♪

32:58.933 --> 33:02.241
Just so you know, this is not me
treating you differently.

33:02.284 --> 33:04.199
♪♪

33:04.243 --> 33:06.201
[ Sighs ]

33:06.245 --> 33:11.250
♪♪

33:11.293 --> 33:12.991
I got you.

33:13.034 --> 33:18.822
♪♪

33:18.866 --> 33:22.130
Correct me if I'm wrong,
but...

33:22.174 --> 33:25.394
that's your penis
touching my penis, right?

33:25.438 --> 33:29.050
[ Chuckles ]
You can't help it, huh?

33:29.094 --> 33:30.921
[ Exhales sharply ]

33:30.965 --> 33:33.794
Man, this guy really loves
his paisley, huh?

33:36.318 --> 33:37.537
Hey, sorry about
what Anna said.

33:37.580 --> 33:38.886
She's just nervous.

33:38.929 --> 33:40.975
Oh, I don't care about
what she said, Eddie.

33:41.019 --> 33:43.934
What I care about is
how much she's drinking.

33:43.978 --> 33:45.501
Oh, it's fine.
I'm driving.

33:45.545 --> 33:47.808
That's not what I mean.

33:47.851 --> 33:49.462
She's at a party.

33:49.505 --> 33:54.380
Yeah, and the guy she's
here with is an alcoholic.

33:54.423 --> 33:56.512
You guys all drink
around me.

33:56.556 --> 33:58.210
Not like that,
we don't.

33:58.253 --> 34:02.127
All I'm saying is, you've done
a lot of work to get sober

34:02.170 --> 34:04.607
and to get your visitation
with Theo back --

34:04.651 --> 34:06.914
Katherine,
with all due respect,

34:06.957 --> 34:08.785
I take my drug tests
and I pass them.

34:08.829 --> 34:10.874
The rest of this is really
none of your business.

34:10.918 --> 34:15.140
♪♪

34:19.840 --> 34:24.323
♪♪

34:24.366 --> 34:28.631
♪♪

34:28.675 --> 34:30.503
[ Hand claps ]

34:30.546 --> 34:32.113
When was it decided
that doctors could just be late

34:32.157 --> 34:34.159
and we all had to be
fine with that?

34:34.202 --> 34:36.204
I mean, the guy did save
your life two years ago.

34:36.248 --> 34:37.379
[ Sighs ]

34:37.423 --> 34:40.426
Maybe cut him
a little slack.

34:40.469 --> 34:41.644
I'll give him
five more minutes.

34:41.688 --> 34:43.211
[ Chuckles ]
Great.

34:43.255 --> 34:44.691
That's just enough time
for me to tell you my theory

34:44.734 --> 34:45.909
about his
perpetual tardiness.

34:45.953 --> 34:47.389
Oh, I'm listening.

34:47.433 --> 34:49.783
He is in cahoots with
the parking people.

34:49.826 --> 34:51.741
First 20 minutes free?

34:51.785 --> 34:54.266
[ Scoffs ]
Not with this guy.

34:54.309 --> 34:57.399
Or maybe it's because
he wants to make an entrance.

34:57.443 --> 34:59.140
No, that's not it.

34:59.184 --> 35:01.316
Could be it.

35:01.360 --> 35:02.752
No, but it's not.

35:02.796 --> 35:04.319
I mean, I can see him
wanting to do that

35:04.363 --> 35:05.886
if he were
dressed differently,

35:05.929 --> 35:09.324
but every day with this guy,
it's the same white lab coat.

35:11.065 --> 35:14.112
Maybe it's the shoes.

35:14.155 --> 35:16.157
I never noticed
the shoes.

35:16.201 --> 35:18.855
Which is exactly why
he needs to make an entrance.

35:18.899 --> 35:21.162
Eh?

35:21.206 --> 35:22.816
[ Door opens ]

35:22.859 --> 35:23.643
Dr. Stein:
Sorry for the wait.

35:26.559 --> 35:27.777
[ Whispers ]
It's the parking.

35:27.821 --> 35:29.257
[ Chuckles ]

35:29.301 --> 35:31.477
So, we got the lab results
right here.

35:31.520 --> 35:35.350
[ Sighs ][ Keyboard clacking ]

35:35.394 --> 35:39.180
It turns out the mass Dr. Jacobs
removed wasn't cancerous.

35:39.224 --> 35:40.747
[ Gasps ]

35:40.790 --> 35:42.183
Thank God.
Thank God.

35:42.227 --> 35:44.620
[ Chuckles ]

35:44.664 --> 35:46.187
You were worried.

35:46.231 --> 35:49.190
By the way,
nice shoes.

35:49.234 --> 35:51.758
[ Chuckles ]

35:51.801 --> 35:53.716
[ Video game car revving]

35:57.633 --> 35:59.418
[ Video game turns off ]

35:59.461 --> 36:01.246
Well?

36:01.289 --> 36:04.684
Well, I won't be leaving you
that game console anytime soon,

36:04.727 --> 36:06.120
if that's what
you're wondering.

36:06.164 --> 36:07.034
[ Door shuts ][ TV remote clicks ]

36:07.077 --> 36:10.211
The doc says I'm fine.

36:10.255 --> 36:11.691
That's amazing.

36:11.734 --> 36:14.781
I -- Ooh! My boobs are
a work in progress, though.

36:14.824 --> 36:15.912
[ Winces ]Sorry.

36:15.956 --> 36:17.305
[ Chuckles ]

36:17.349 --> 36:18.480
Colin, don't get up.

36:18.524 --> 36:22.310
It was just
a life-or-death situation.

36:22.354 --> 36:23.877
They got the whole tumor?

36:23.920 --> 36:25.705
Yeah,
with clear margins.

36:25.748 --> 36:28.098
Oh, thank God.

36:28.142 --> 36:30.318
Can I text everyone
the good news?

36:30.362 --> 36:32.277
As long as you keep me off
the group chain.

36:32.320 --> 36:35.584
♪♪

36:35.628 --> 36:37.543
Hey, Dan Dixon...

36:39.240 --> 36:43.549
Thank you
for telling Sophie.

36:43.592 --> 36:45.507
I'm just glad
you're okay.

36:45.551 --> 36:46.943
Now can I have
my socks back?

36:46.987 --> 36:48.249
I don't
see that happening.

36:48.293 --> 36:49.555
[ Chuckles ]

36:49.598 --> 36:54.342
♪♪

36:54.386 --> 36:55.343
Let me see.

36:55.387 --> 36:57.215
[ Gasps ]

36:57.258 --> 36:59.347
Oh, I know exactly
what I would've charaded

36:59.391 --> 37:01.131
for Martin Scorsese.
[ Chuckles ]

37:01.175 --> 37:03.395
Next time.
Really?

37:03.438 --> 37:04.265
[ Knock on door ]

37:04.309 --> 37:06.267
Ooh!
Hold that thought.

37:09.444 --> 37:10.967
Who is Stephen Root?

37:11.011 --> 37:12.273
[ Door opens ]

37:12.317 --> 37:14.841
Oh, he must be on
one of those kid shows.

37:14.884 --> 37:16.495
[ Door closes ]

37:16.538 --> 37:22.327
♪♪

37:22.370 --> 37:25.068
I didn't realize you two were --
so I will just --

37:25.112 --> 37:26.896
I will -- I will
get out of the way.

37:26.940 --> 37:29.769
No, Shelly,
don't -- don't leave.

37:29.812 --> 37:31.205
I came here
to see you.

37:33.033 --> 37:34.991
I mean,
"None of my business"?

37:35.035 --> 37:37.907
All I was doing was trying
to look out for his sobriety.

37:37.951 --> 37:40.258
She was a mess, right?
Like a total mess.

37:40.301 --> 37:42.434
She wasa mess.
You're right about that.

37:42.477 --> 37:44.784
Yeah, and then,
he just --[ Objects clatter ]

37:44.827 --> 37:48.701
Wait, um, wh-what
am I notright about?

37:48.744 --> 37:52.444
Last night, the reason
you didn't give anyone
a heads up about us

37:52.487 --> 37:54.489
is because I'm
the person you're dating,

37:54.533 --> 37:56.099
and everybody has to either
accept that or not.

37:56.143 --> 37:57.710
I know where you're
going with this,

37:57.753 --> 37:59.494
and this is
completely different.

37:59.538 --> 38:02.454
It's not about me liking her
or not liking her.

38:02.497 --> 38:05.021
I'm worried about
him relapsing.

38:05.065 --> 38:08.677
Are you sure that is
the only reason you're upset?

38:08.721 --> 38:11.071
Because it seems like maybe
this is the first big decision

38:11.114 --> 38:13.421
that Eddie's made without you
since you've gotten divorced,

38:13.465 --> 38:15.162
and you are having
a hard time letting go.

38:15.205 --> 38:17.338
[ Scoffs ]
That is not true.

38:17.382 --> 38:19.166
It kind of is.

38:19.209 --> 38:20.515
Didn't you say
he showed you the apartment

38:20.559 --> 38:21.516
he was gonna rent?

38:21.560 --> 38:23.475
Because hewanted to.

38:23.518 --> 38:25.868
Okay, but he didn't
ask you to bring

38:25.912 --> 38:27.870
a non-alcoholic drink
to the party for him.

38:29.916 --> 38:32.048
You're acting like
you are still married to him.

38:32.092 --> 38:34.050
Believe me, I-I know
how difficult it can be

38:34.094 --> 38:36.749
to break the habit
of taking care of someone.

38:36.792 --> 38:38.751
I mean, the first couple weeks
after Julia and I split,

38:38.794 --> 38:40.927
she texted me
every night

38:40.970 --> 38:43.277
to make sure that
I was taking my meds.

38:43.321 --> 38:45.975
But being bipolar
and being an alcoholic

38:46.019 --> 38:48.500
are two completely
different things.

38:48.543 --> 38:50.545
You're right,
but they are two things

38:50.589 --> 38:52.547
we both have to
constantly prove to the world

38:52.591 --> 38:55.202
we have under control.

38:55.245 --> 38:57.987
Which is tough
when the people that we love

38:58.031 --> 39:01.426
respond the way that --
that you and Julia do.

39:01.469 --> 39:02.905
I'm in a good place.

39:02.949 --> 39:04.429
It seems like
Eddie is, too.

39:04.472 --> 39:08.128
But he will never be able
to prove it to you, or himself,

39:08.171 --> 39:11.044
if you don't
give him a chance.

39:11.087 --> 39:13.786
♪♪

39:13.829 --> 39:15.744
[ Sighs ]

39:15.788 --> 39:16.963
[ Pills rattle ]

39:17.006 --> 39:18.747
♪♪

39:18.791 --> 39:21.663
So,
how're you feeling?

39:24.100 --> 39:28.235
Embarrassed and like
a truck just ran me over.

39:28.278 --> 39:30.106
That happened
to me once.

39:30.150 --> 39:32.065
[ Chuckles ]

39:32.108 --> 39:34.197
Ouch.

39:34.241 --> 39:37.897
Eddie,
I'm...so sorry.

39:37.940 --> 39:39.681
It's just,
seeing the connection

39:39.725 --> 39:41.248
that you still have
with Katherine

39:41.291 --> 39:43.250
and then being so nervous
to be around all your friends,

39:43.293 --> 39:46.688
I probably --

39:46.732 --> 39:48.603
I had a little
too much to drink.

39:48.647 --> 39:50.605
Been there, too.

39:50.649 --> 39:54.783
Listen, I need to talk to you
about something.

39:54.827 --> 39:58.178
I was at my support group
yesterday,

39:58.221 --> 39:59.179
and I brought you up.

39:59.222 --> 40:00.441
Oh.

40:00.485 --> 40:05.751
And when I did,
I called you "my Anna."

40:05.794 --> 40:07.317
My Anna?

40:07.361 --> 40:12.453
Yeah, I was gonna say
"my girlfriend,"

40:12.497 --> 40:15.804
but then I realized I didn't
talk to you about that yet,

40:15.848 --> 40:17.415
and...

40:17.458 --> 40:20.418
How would you feel if,

40:20.461 --> 40:25.335
next time,
I say "my girlfriend"?

40:25.379 --> 40:28.295
I think I'd like that.

40:28.338 --> 40:31.994
Okay, girlfriend.

40:32.038 --> 40:35.476
Oh, I-I do
like it a lot...

40:35.520 --> 40:37.304
boyfriend.

40:37.347 --> 40:38.740
I never said
you could call me that.

40:38.784 --> 40:40.133
[ Both laugh ]

40:40.176 --> 40:45.051
♪ Ooh-ooh

40:45.094 --> 40:47.749
Ronald:
Shelly, I am so sorry.

40:47.793 --> 40:49.490
I wish I knew what
you were going through

40:49.534 --> 40:51.971
when we were together.

40:52.014 --> 40:55.888
But the one thing
I need you to know is,

40:55.931 --> 40:57.672
I believe you.

40:57.716 --> 41:01.763
♪ I need time to move on

41:01.807 --> 41:06.551
♪ I need love to feel strong

41:06.594 --> 41:12.644
♪ 'Cause I've had time
to think it through, and ♪

41:12.687 --> 41:18.214
♪ Ooh ♪ Do you believe
in life after love? ♪

41:18.258 --> 41:20.521
What are you thinking about,
Mendez?

41:20.565 --> 41:27.006
Oh, just -- just
thinking about you.

41:27.049 --> 41:28.529
And all the moments
since we broke up

41:28.573 --> 41:29.704
that we could've
been together.

41:32.794 --> 41:35.580
I don't want to waste
any more time.

41:35.623 --> 41:38.713
I think...

41:38.757 --> 41:40.236
we should just
move back in together.

41:40.280 --> 41:43.718
♪♪

41:43.762 --> 41:45.503
I think we should
have a baby.

41:45.546 --> 41:51.334
♪ Ooh ♪ Do you believe
in life after love? ♪

41:51.378 --> 41:54.033
♪ Do you believe
in life after love? ♪

41:54.076 --> 41:55.034
Yeah?

41:55.077 --> 41:56.557
Mm-hmm.

41:56.601 --> 41:59.865
Well, if it's a boy,
obviously, it's Camden.

41:59.908 --> 42:02.215
[ Laughs ]

42:02.258 --> 42:05.784
What will we name it
if it's a girl?♪ I really don't think
you're strong enough ♪

42:11.224 --> 42:18.274
♪♪

